Sharjah Islamic Bank Hires HSBC, StanChart for Sukuk Sale

-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 
2011-05-08T04:54:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/sharjah-islamic-bank-hires-hsbc-stanchart-for-sukuk-sale.html
Sharjah Islamic Bank (NBS)  PJSC, a United
Arab Emirates lender, hired  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  and  Standard
Chartered Plc (STAN)  to manage the sale of Islamic bonds.  The dollar-denominated sukuk will be sold subject to market
conditions and after fixed-income investor meetings in the
Middle East, Asia and Europe, the Sharjah-based bank said in a
statement to the Abu Dhabi bourse today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shaji Mathew in Dubai at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Riad Hamade at 
 rhamade@bloomberg.net  